# Detailed Technical Report

## Resume Screening & Job Matching System — Frontend Implementation

---

## 1. Project Context

The project already had a working FastAPI backend and a basic React frontend. The backend exposed two endpoints:

| Endpoint | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `POST /predict` | Accepts resume text + optional job description → returns predicted job category, confidence score, TF-IDF cosine similarity match score, and top terms from both documents |
| `GET /categories` | Returns all 25+ job categories the ML model knows about |

The original frontend only had a single-page flow: upload a resume → click Analyze → see a basic results page. There was no editing, no structured job description config, no recruiter view, and no dark mode.

**Goal:** Rebuild the frontend into a full dual-view product (Candidate + Recruiter) while keeping **zero backend changes**.

