## 3. What Was Planned First

A full implementation plan was drafted before writing any code. The key design decisions made upfront:

> **No backend changes.** Every feature — including the recruiter dashboard — was designed to work purely with the two existing endpoints.

> **Recruiter dashboard uses session storage.** Since there's no server-side candidate database, each time a resume is matched, the result is pushed into a `sessionStorage`-backed Zustand array. The recruiter table reads from there.

> **Matching/missing skills are derived client-side.** The `/predict` endpoint returns `resume_top_terms` and `jd_top_terms`. The frontend computes the intersection (matching) and difference (missing) locally.

> **Job recommendations are synthesised.** They come from `/categories` + the match score, not a separate AI endpoint.

