### 4.2 State Management

#### `src/store.js` — *Extended*

The Zustand store was expanded from 5 state slices to 9:

```
Auth slice          ← unchanged (user, login, logout, openAuthModal)
Dark Mode slice     ← new (darkMode boolean, toggleDarkMode)
View slice          ← new (view: 'candidate'|'recruiter')
Resume Upload slice ← unchanged (resumeFile, resumeText, jobDescription, analysisResult, isAnalyzing)
Parsed Resume slice ← NEW (parsedResume, setParsedResume, updateParsedResume)
Job Config slice    ← NEW (jobConfig: { jdText, requiredSkills[], experienceMin, experienceMax, role })
Match Result slice  ← NEW (matchResult, setMatchResult)
Candidates slice    ← NEW (candidates[], addCandidate, clearCandidates) — sessionStorage-backed
Step slice          ← NEW (step 1-4, nextStep, prevStep, setStep)
```

**Dark mode toggle logic:**

```js
toggleDarkMode: () =>
  set((state) => {
    const next = !state.darkMode
    localStorage.setItem('rs_dark', String(next))
    // Directly mutate the DOM — Tailwind reads html.dark
    if (next) document.documentElement.classList.add('dark')
    else      document.documentElement.classList.remove('dark')
    return { darkMode: next }
  })
```

**Candidates session persistence:**

```js
addCandidate: (candidate) =>
  set((s) => {
    const updated = [candidate, ...s.candidates].slice(0, 50) // max 50
    sessionStorage.setItem('rs_candidates', JSON.stringify(updated))
    return { candidates: updated }
  })
```

