#### `ParsedResumeEditor.jsx` — *New*

Displays editable extracted resume fields. Uses `updateParsedResume(patch)` to do partial store updates (React pattern: merge patch, not replace).

| Field | Input Type |
|---|---|
| Name | Text input |
| Skills | `SkillTagInput` |
| Education | Text input |
| Experience | Range slider (0–20 years) |
| Preferred Role | Text input |

**How it gets data:** `CandidatePage` runs a heuristic parser on the raw extracted text when it detects `resumeText` has been set and `parsedResume` is still null:

```js
useEffect(() => {
  if (resumeText && !parsedResume) {
    setParsedResume(extractResumeFields(resumeText))
  }
}, [resumeText, parsedResume, setParsedResume])
```

The parser uses regex/keyword matching — it's not ML, it's heuristic pattern matching to give a fast starting point that the user can correct.

