#### `src/pages/CandidatePage.jsx` — *New*

The most complex page. It orchestrates all 4 steps.

**Step Indicator** — renders 4 dots connected by lines, using `.step-dot.active`, `.step-dot.done`, `.step-dot.pending` CSS classes from `index.css`.

**Resume parsing function** (`extractResumeFields`):

```js
// Name: first line ≤40 chars matching a name-like regex
const nameLine = lines.find(l => l.length <= 40 && /^[A-Za-z ,.'-]{2,}$/.test(l))

// Education: line containing degree keyword
const edu = lines.find(l => /b\.?tech|bachelor|master|phd.../i.test(l))

// Experience: search for "X years" pattern
const expMatch = text.match(/(\d+)\s*\+?\s*years?/i)

// Skills: match against a hardcoded list of 40+ tech keywords
const skills = skillKeywords.filter(k => lowerText.includes(k))
```

**Job Recommendations builder** (`buildRecommendations`):

```js
categories.map(cat => ({
  title: cat,
  // Predicted category gets the real score; others get a randomised lower score
  matchPct: cap(baseScore * (cat === category ? 1 : 0.55 + Math.random() * 0.3)),
  skills: matchResult.resumeTopTerms.slice(0, 6)
})).sort((a,b) => b.matchPct - a.matchPct).slice(0, 6)
```

