## 5. Data Flow Diagram

```
User uploads PDF/DOCX
       │
       ▼
DropZone (pdfjs-dist / mammoth)
extracts raw text → store.resumeText
       │
       ▼
CandidatePage useEffect
runs extractResumeFields(text)
→ store.parsedResume { name, skills, education, experience, role }
       │
       ▼
User edits in ParsedResumeEditor
→ store.updateParsedResume(patch)
       │
       ▼
User fills JobConfigPanel
→ store.setJobConfig({ jdText, requiredSkills, experienceMin, experienceMax, role })
       │
       ▼
Click "Match Resume"
→ useMatch.mutate({ resumeText, jobDescription: jdText || requiredSkills.join(' ') })
       │
       ▼
POST /predict
returns { predicted_category, confidence, match_score, resume_top_terms, jd_top_terms }
       │
       ├──► deriveSkillSets() → { matching[], missing[] }
       ├──► buildRecommendation() → natural language string
       └──► store.setMatchResult({ matchScore, matchingSkills, missingSkills, recommendation, ... })
       │
       └──► store.addCandidate({ name, matchScore, skills, experience, category })
                  │
                  ▼
           sessionStorage['rs_candidates']
                  │
                  ▼
           RecruiterPage → CandidateTable reads candidates[]
```

