## 6. Patterns & Decisions Summary

| Decision | Rationale |
|---|---|
| Zustand over Redux | Less boilerplate; the app doesn't need Redux DevTools complexity |
| React Query for API calls | Handles caching, loading/error states, and retry automatically |
| `sessionStorage` for candidates | Persists across page navigations within a tab; cleared on tab close — appropriate for a demo tool |
| Heuristic resume parsing | The backend returns raw TF-IDF terms, not structured NER. Client-side regex gives a usable starting point without adding a new endpoint |
| CSS component classes over Tailwind utilities | Long className strings hurt readability; `.glass-card`, `.tag-pill`, `.step-dot` are more expressive |
| Derived data in hooks, not pages | `useMatch` owns all the derivation logic (skills, recommendation, candidate save). `CandidatePage` just calls it — separation of concerns |
| Dark mode via `html.dark` class | Tailwind's `darkMode: 'class'` is the standard pattern; CSS custom properties in `:root` handle transitions smoothly |

